  "hasSensitivityAnalysisRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/sensitivity/cou2-mrl5-sa",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis for CFD hemolysis prediction — MRL 5",
    "description": "A Sobol variance-based global sensitivity analysis (N=4096 quasi-random samples, Saltelli sampling scheme) was performed varying eight model inputs: blood dynamic viscosity (±8%), pump rotational speed (±2%), inlet flow rate (±5%), gap clearance geometry (±50 µm), turbulence model constant C_µ (±15%), red blood cell fragility threshold stress (±20%), hemolysis power-law exponent α (±10%), and outlet pressure boundary condition (±3%). The dominant first-order sensitivity indices were: hemolysis power-law exponent α (S₁=0.41), RBC fragility threshold (S₁=0.28), and gap clearance geometry (S₁=0.17). Total-order indices confirmed negligible higher-order interactions for flow rate and viscosity. The analysis demonstrates that hemolysis predictions are most sensitive to constitutive model parameters, motivating the high rigor applied to model-form and model-input credibility factors."
  },
