      "description": "The CFD model is applicable only to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry as defined in the ASTM F1841 reference geometry dataset. Application is restricted to Newtonian blood analog fluids with hematocrit 35–45% and temperature 36–38°C. The model is not applicable to pulsatile flow regimes, non-Newtonian shear-thinning fluids, or pump geometries with impeller diameter deviating more than ±5% from the reference 52 mm nominal. Extrapolation beyond the validated operating envelope defined in hasOperatingEnvelope is explicitly excluded."
